OL,3,CEconomy grows less than previously
OL,4,Cthought, figures show
OL,6,FGrowth across the UK economy was
OL,7,Fweaker than previously thought over
OL,8,Fthe spring, according to revised
OL,9,Fofficial figures.
OL,11,FThe Office for National Statistics
OL,12,F(ONS) said gross domestic product
OL,13,F(GDP) increased by 0.5% between April
OL,14,Fand June, revised down from an initial
OL,15,Festimate of 0.6%.
OL,17,FGrowth was driven by an increase in
OL,18,Fthe services sector, while the
OL,19,Fmanufacturing and construction
OL,20,Findustries dragged on the headline
OL,21,Ffigure, the ONS said.
