OL,6,FThe figures show that the UK economy
OL,7,Fcontinued its recovery from recession
OL,8,Fat the end of last year, albeit at a
OL,9,Fslightly slower pace than previously
OL,10,Fthought.
OL,12,FA technical recession is defined as
OL,13,Ftwo consecutive quarters of negative
OL,14,Fgrowth.
OL,16,FGDP increased by 0.7% over the first
OL,17,Fquarter, between January and March,
OL,18,Funrevised figures showed, marking the
OL,19,Fend of the shallow recessionary period.
