OL,3,CEconomy grows less than previously
OL,4,Cthought, figures show
OL,6,F"Our latest data show that household
OL,7,Fsavings continue to increase and are
OL,8,Fnow at their highest rate since the
OL,9,FCovid-19 lockdowns.
OL,11,F"The household saving ratio is
OL,12,Festimated at 10% in the latest
OL,13,Fquarter, up from 8.9% over the start
OL,14,Fof the year, meaning people were
OL,15,Fkeeping more of their disposable
OL,16,Fincome locked into savings.
OL,18,FMore recent data shows that the
OL,19,Feconomy has been flatlining, with no
OL,20,Fgrowth recorded in both June and July.
